    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-05-30T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-05-30T12:00:00-05:00" n="190"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d190">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/68: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-05-30T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 30, 1934—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 30—3:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>287. Department’s 211, May 24, 3 p.m.<note n="54" xml:id="d190fn54">See telegram
                        No. 202, May 24, 3 p.m., to the Ambassador in France, <ref target="#pg_239"
                            >p. 239</ref>.</note> The Japanese Ambassador informed me today he was
                    accepting the British invitation [along?] very much the same lines as our
                    reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
